.TH "WEBGLRENDERINGCONTEXT.HINT" "3JS" "September 28, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebGLRenderingContext.hint \- WebGLRenderingContext: hint() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]WebGLRenderingContext.hint()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
WebGL API specifies hints for certain behaviors.
The interpretation of these hints depend on the implementation.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
hint(target, mode)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]target\f[R]
Sets which behavior to be controlled.
Possible values:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]gl.GENERATE_MIPMAP_HINT\f[R]
Quality of filtering when generating mipmap images with
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.generateMipmap()\f[R].
.PP
When using the \f[CR]OES_standard_derivatives\f[R] extension:
.TP
\f[B]ext.FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT_OES\f[R]
Accuracy of the derivative calculation for the GLSL built\-in functions:
\f[CR]dFdx\f[R], \f[CR]dFdy\f[R], and \f[CR]fwidth\f[R].
.PP
When using a WebGL 2 context, the following values are available
additionally:
.TP
\f[B]gl.FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT\f[R]
Same as \f[CR]ext.FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT_OES\f[R]
.RE
.TP
\f[B]mode\f[R]
Sets the behavior.
The default value is \f[CR]gl.DONT_CARE\f[R].
The possible values are:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.FASTEST\f[R]: The most efficient behavior should be used.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.NICEST\f[R]: The most correct or the highest quality option
should be used.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.DONT_CARE\f[R]: There is no preference for this behavior.
.RE
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
The following example hints that the quality of filtering when
generating mipmap images should be most efficient instead of the best
quality.
.IP
.EX
gl.hint(gl.GENERATE_MIPMAP_HINT, gl.FASTEST);
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.generateMipmap()\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
